column8: P1. There are too many mental health services in Switzerland, and they should be reduced.
column9: P2. There are enough mental health services in Switzerland, and funding should remain as it is.
column10: P3. Initiatives focused on improving the socioeconomic conditions of disadvantaged people should be implemented to address mental health disparities.
column11: P4. Private mental health clinics should receive more government funding to allow more people to access them.
column12: P5. There should be more public awareness campaigns that empower people to seek mental health support and destigmatize help-seeking behaviors.
column13: P6. There should be more integrated mental health clinics that provide a range of services, such as sports or artistic activities in addition to therapy and medication
column14: P7. There are not enough mental health services in Switzerland, so their funding should be increased.
